import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.array([80, 85, 90, 95, 100, 105, 110, 115, 120, 125])
y = np.array([240, 250, 260, 270, 280, 290, 300, 310, 320, 330])

plt.title("Sports Watch Data")
plt.xlabel("Average Pulse")
plt.ylabel("Calorie Burnage")

plt.plot(x, y)

plt.grid(axis = 'y')

plt.show()

#sine waves using matplotlib 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
x = np.arange(0,4*np.pi)   # start,stop,step
y = np.sin(x)
plt.plot(x, y,c='hotpink',marker='s',mfc='g')
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig=plt.figure()
axes1=fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])
axes2=fig.add_axes([0.10,0.6,0.4,0.3])
axes1.plot(x,y2,'r')

axes1.set_ylabel('Earnings',fontsize=15)
